The paper deals with a problem in artificial intelligence related to planning under uncertainty in a partially observable environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for learning a model of the environment directly from action-observation pairs, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of a simulated mobile robot planning task suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper also deals with prediction in a high-dimensional, vision-based environment, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the use of a Predictive State Representation (PSR) suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
